  "texts": [
    "FAFA, has been one of the most widely used SCMs in concrete since the 1930s.",
    "As a by-product of coal combustion in power plants, FA is highly valued for its pozzolanic properties, which enhance the durability and sulfate resistance of cementbased materials while also improving their long-term strength and workability [34].",
    "The production of FA begins with the burning of non-hazardous volatile materials and carbon present in coal.",
    "This process takes place in a furnace, where the minerals and impurities in the coal combine with exhaust gases.",
    "As these gases cool, the components solidify to form FA."
  ],
